THE PRIVACY POLICY
In Wild Spike, we highly appreciate the safety of your Personal Data. This Privacy Policy governs the handling of Wild Spike, LLC, hereinafter – “Wild Spike”, (“our”, “us”, “we”) with your Personal Data during the use of our games for mobile devices and tablet computers, hereinafter referred to as “the Services”, including their collection, use and processing methods.
This Policy has been developed in accordance with the current legislation of the Republic of Belarus, according to which the Wild Spike, LLC is a Personal Data processor. We would like to draw your attention to the fact, that this Policy applies only if you use our Services and agree to all the provisions of the Policy. Please, do not use the Services if you do not agree to this Policy.
This Privacy Policy applies to all Services we provide on websites, mobile apps or any other platforms or devices.
You accept and agree that Wild Spike reserves the right to update and modify this Privacy Policy, all changes taking effect immediately after publication on the website at the following address:
https://www.wildspike.com
. We recommend that you check
https://www.wildspike.com
occasionally for published changes in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms and/or provisions of this Privacy Policy, please do not provide your Personal Data and do not use the Wild Spike Services.
PERSONAL DATA AND INFORMATION PROCESSING AND STORAGE
Our principal purpose of collecting Personal Data and information is to provide you with access to our Applications/Games and improve them and related services (collectively referred to as “the Services”). We process your Personal Data with the consent you give when registering, as well as when using our Services.
Depending on which of our Services you use, we may collect and process the data provided by you during registration, when using the Services, as well as when contacting us, for example:
your name, email address or other contact information that you provide to us (“Through Contact Us/email”);
if you access the Services using the function Facebook Connect, Apple game center, Google Play Games or other, provided by the platform on which our Services are hosted, we receive publicly available information from your account, such as: your first and last name or nickname, profile page ID and profile images /URL
other data that you will provide to us in the Services, or by e-mail on your initiative.
Please note that the Personal Data that you voluntarily make public in your user profile, or disclose leaving comments, will be available to everyone and can be viewed by others. We do not accept any responsibility for any information that you voluntarily disclose by such and/or other explicit actions.
Your account can be used for public identification when using social functions of the Services, for example, when interacting between the users, publishing public ratings, personal competitions, etc.
Information received by the support service
If you contact our support service support@wildspike.com for assistance, we store the contact information provided by you (usually your name and email address), information about your gameplay or activity in the Services, as well as the user’s name/nickname. Moreover, we keep all correspondence and the information contained therein.
Use of your information by third parties.
We may share your information with the external entities that provide certain services to us, including, but not limited to, hosting, payment processing, analytics, as well as marketing services. By transferring your information to external service providers and business partners, we guarantee the presence of agreements on the protection of your information, which are required by the data protection legislation in force.
Advertising.
When advertising is displayed in our Services, we may allow advertising networks of our affiliates and partner networks to collect information about your mobile device. This allows showing targeted advertising to you. The following information is processed:
device manufacturer, model and operating system;
screen size and orientation;
name and properties of the mobile application through which the user interacts with the Services;
country, time zone and language settings (country and preferred language);
type and speed of network connection;
IP address;
Internet browser used to access the Services;
advertising identifier (IDFA on iOS devices and GAID on Android devices.
In order for us to provide in-game advertising, we may send your advertising ID and IP address, data from cookies and other similar technologies, as well as other such information to advertisers (or advertising networks). They could then find advertisements that are suitable for you to display in our games and on the off-site resources. You can control and restrict our use of your advertising ID using the settings on your device. Wild Spike, LLC does not control which specific advertisements will be shown in our games (this is controlled by advertising networks), but we block certain categories of advertisements.
