HOW WE USE YOUR DATA
We process your Personal Data for the following legitimate business purposes:
to provide and manage our Services;
to create user accounts/profiles that will allow you to play our games and use our Services, if necessary;
to send you messages related to the Services (e.g., regarding changes, updates, new functions);
to verify and confirm payments (we do not collect or store credit card information, our payment service providers provide us with information about your purchases so that we know if the payment has been completed);
to provide suitable versions of our games (e.g., games in the required language);
to respond to your support requests (e.g., if you address a complaint or comment to us).
At required by the legislation for the purposes of ensuring the security and transparency of social functions of the Services, combating fraud, as well as providing acceptable use, and namely:
to prevent and/or detect illegal activities, deceit or fraudulent behavior;
to take measures against players committing fraudulent or deceptive actions, as well as against illegal activities (including hacking or cheating).
To improve the operation of the Services, taking into account our players’ preferences:
to conduct research, testing, optimization, development and improvement of the Services and player experience;
to keep information secure for your subsequent authentication when using the Services;
to receive error data that you/your device encounter when using our Services, and to correct malfunctions and interoperability problems;
to process and analyze information in order to better understand your preferences and improve the quality of your gaming experience and satisfaction level when using our Services. We may also collect statistics on your engagement with the community, for example, whether you view messages or which links you click on;
if you interact with us through a social network or community pages, to obtain information and use it to manage our social network and community pages, including to interact with you, and we may also share your posts on these pages, subject to your consent.
Personal Data and information security and safety.
We aim to conserve the security of data collected by any means available to us, and, therefore, we have taken all necessary measures and steps in accordance with industry standards, in particular, we used encryption, where appropriate. Your Personal Data and transactions are protected from unauthorized access, misuse or any modifications.
How can you update or manage your personal information.
If your information is incomplete, overdue, incorrect or irrelevant, and you want to make any changes, you can send your request to support@wildspike.com. This email address can also be used if you need to appeal or have any questions regarding your Personal Data or this Privacy Policy.
Data storage
Your data will be stored in our system over the entire period of time that your account is active or for the time necessary to provide you with the Services. Please note that when receiving a request for your data deletion, we will continue to store it as anonymous information after your account is deleted. Any information that you have shared with other users of our Services, such as in-game correspondence, correspondence with technical support or any other content available to other users, will remain available in the system after your data is deleted.
We may send you occasional push notifications in our Services. This is usually information about game updates and high scores, or other information about Services that may be important to you. You can opt-out of the receipt of such notifications at any time by disabling them in your device settings.
Special information
We do not request and do not intend to collect any “special information”, for example, information related to health, race, religion, political views or philosophical beliefs, sexual preferences or orientation. Please be careful and do not to share such information about yourself (or others) when using our Services.
You can control and restrict the nature of the Personal Data that we collect and process in several ways. For example, you can disconnect your social media account from our games or manage your privacy settings in social networks to limit the extent of information transmitted to us. You can also disable your mobile advertising ID or in the whole limit advertising tracking by using the settings on your device. You can also limit or disable the use of cookies (or similar technologies).
Personal Data deletion
You have the right to request and receive the deletion of your Personal Data collected within or through our Services.
If you would like to exercise this right, please send your request to support@wildspike.com (please note that if your request is sent to any other Wild Spike email address, we cannot guarantee its receipt and further processing). We will try to respond to your request within 30 days after we receive such a request. If you would like us to respond to your request within a shorter period of time, established by the law, please send a request in the form specified in the section below. In order to exercise your right, we will need to identify you as the owner of the account. You understand and agree that for these purposes we will have to request additional information from you, such as photos and/or copies of your documents, which you undertake to provide. The provision of these documents is necessary to avoid fraud, as well as to prevent your account from any potential harm.
Please note that the deletion of your Personal Data will be accompanied by the deletion of all related information, such as your in-game progress, including the level achieved, purchased subscriptions to in-game content (including those purchased for real money) and any other in-game content related to your account. Restoration will be impossible. Requesting your Personal Data deletion, you understand and accept this fact and confirm the deletion of all related information.
YOUR RIGHTS
You, as a Personal Data subject, have the right to:
withdraw your consent to the Personal Data processing;
receive information regarding your Personal Data processing and Personal Data changing;
receive information about the provision of your Personal Data to third parties;
require to stop your Personal Data processing and (or) their deletion;
appeal against our actions (failure to act) and decisions related to your Personal Data processing.
To exercise your rights mentioned above, you can send us an application in writing or in an electronic form.
Such application should contain:
your surname, first name, and patronymic, residence address;
your date of birth;
statement of the essence of your requirements;
your personal or electronic digital signature.
YOUR DATA PROTECTION RIGHTS UNDER THE GENERAL DATA PROTECTION REGULATION (GDPR)
If you are a resident of the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain data protection rights. Wildspike  aims to take reasonable steps to allow you to correct, amend, delete or limit the use of your Personal Data.
If you wish to be informed about what Personal Data we hold about you and if you want it to be removed from our systems, please contact us.
In certain circumstances, you have the following data protection rights:
The right to access, update or delete the personal information we hold about you.
The right to correct. You have the right to have your information corrected if that information is inaccurate or incomplete.
Right to object. You have the right to object to our processing of your Personal Data.
The right to limit. You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information.
The right to withdraw consent. You also have the right to withdraw your consent at any time WildSpike has relied on your consent to process your personal information. Please note that we may ask you to verify your identity before responding to such requests.
You have the right to complain to a Data Protection Authority about our collection and use of your Personal Data. For more information, please contact your local data protection authority in the European Economic Area (EEA).
HOW YOU CAN CONTACT US
Data controller: Wild Spike, LLC. Should you have any questions about data protection, or you would like to send a request to resolve the problems of your Personal Data, we recommend that you send a request to the support service using our website
https://www.wildspike.com/
or by sending us an email to: support@wildspike.com. We may also ask you to prove your identity before we start processing your request.
